OL,3,CReeves must raise taxes to cover #41bn
OL,4,Cblack hole, warns leading think tank
OL,6,FNIESR says a toxic mix of weaker
OL,7,Feconomic growth, lower tax receipts,
OL,8,Fhigher borrowing, and Labour's failure
OL,9,Fto deliver the welfare savings it
OL,10,Fplanned means the chancellor is now on
OL,11,Ftrack to break one of her own key
OL,12,Ffiscal rules.
OL,14,FThat rule - the so-called "stability
OL,15,Frule" - is Labour's pledge to get the
OL,16,Fcurrent budget into surplus by 2028/
OL,17,F29. That means bringing in more
OL,18,Fthrough taxes and other income than it
OL,19,Fspends on public services and welfare.
