OL,4,Cblack hole, warns leading think tank
OL,6,FCity economists and Westminster
OL,7,Fanalysts broadly agree that the
OL,8,Fgovernment's finances no longer add
OL,9,Fup. But NIESR's assessment is
OL,10,Fparticularly stark: it believes the
OL,11,Fchancellor may now need to find more
OL,12,Fthan #50 billion just to restore the
OL,13,Fwiggle room she had five months ago.
OL,15,FStephen Millard from the NIESR
OL,16,Fbelieves Labour didn't realise how bad
OL,17,Fthe public finances were when they
OL,18,Fcame into power
